<note xml:lang="en">Designs of two horsemen. Above, a very clumsy sketch of a man on a horse, holding a long pole and advancing left. Below, very sketchy outline of a similar figure. 
   Below that, a far more careful depiction of a horse, front legs together, springing to left; 
   the rider, in a long tunic, turns to face the viewer; he has the reins in his right hand and a long ?pole in his left. His hair forms a fringe and bunches on either side of his face.</note>
</div>
